b'' b" i've got this animation file with a .gl extension." b' what is this? are there anu ms-dos or os/2 programs' b' which will run this file? thanks.' b'' b'' b'the gl file is an archive containing individual frames or pieces of' b'frames (usually stored as .pic or .clp files), fonts, and a .txt file' b'that tells the grasp animation system how to display it. gl stands' b'for grasp library. there is probably a detailed discussion of this subject' b'in the alt.binaries.pictures faq.' b'' b'there are freely distributable viewers for gl files, and they are usually' b'named grasprt?.exe (replace the with a version digit or letter). most' b'gl files contain frames that are hardware-specific to particular modes' b'of the cga, ega, or vga adapters on pcs. i think that there are some' b'copies of grasprt available by anonymous ftp (i know that i got one there' b'a long time ago).' b'' b'good luck' b'jack' b'' b'--' b'|| p.o. box b'== ft. lauderdale, fl usa phone: 